Hi

I have an use case where I need to get the value of the removed key on invalidate(). I have stored a Netty direct ByteBuf inside the cache, and it needs to be released so the memory can be returned to the pool. Here is an example

```
var buf = cache.get(key);
if (buf != null) {
    buf.release();
}
cache.invalidate(key);
```

But there might be a race condition, causing the buf not released (e.g when it's created after the call to `get()` but before the call to `invalidate`). If it's a Map, I can use the `remove()` method and get the returned value. But the `invalidate` method of Guava returns void, so it's not possible. The expectation is like this to prevent race condition:

```
var buf = cache.invalidate(key);
if (buf != null)
    buf.release();
```

Note: I rather not used synchronized or any sort of locking, since everywhere else they are already non-blocking.

Both offer similar capability using double-checked idiom. However, it seems that the [Apache LazyInitializer](https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/apidocs/index.html?org/apache/commons/lang3/concurrent/LazyInitializer.html) is 2X faster than Suppliers.memoize in construction. `get()` accessor performs about the same.

Here is code I used to micro-benchmark (using OpenJDK JMH):

```java
import com.google.common.base.*;
import org.openjdk.jmh.annotations.*;
import org.apache.commons.lang3.concurrent.*;

@OutputTimeUnit(java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit.MICROSECONDS)
public class LazySupplierBenchmark {

    @State(Scope.Thread)
    public static class ConstructionState {
        double random = Math.random();
    }

    @Benchmark
    public Supplier<Double> guavaConstruction(final ConstructionState state) {
        return Suppliers.memoize(() -> state.random);
    }

    @Benchmark
    public LazyInitializer<Double> apacheConstruction(final ConstructionState state) {
        return new LazyInitializer<>() {
            @Override
            protected Double initialize() throws ConcurrentException {
                return state.random;
            }
        };
    }


    @State(Scope.Thread)
    public static class InitializerState {
        Supplier<Double> guava;
        LazyInitializer<Double> apache;

        @Setup(Level.Invocation) // new instance each time
        public void setup() {
            guava = Suppliers.memoize(Math::random);
            apache = new LazyInitializer<>() {
                @Override
                protected Double initialize() {
                    return Math.random();
                }
            };
        }
    }

    @Benchmark
    public Double guavaInitialize(final InitializerState state) {
        return state.guava.get();
    }

    @Benchmark
    public Double apacheInitialize(final InitializerState state) throws ConcurrentException {
        return state.apache.get();
    }


    @State(Scope.Thread)
    public static class CacheState {
        Supplier<Double> guava = Suppliers.memoize(Math::random);
        LazyInitializer<Double> apache = new LazyInitializer<>() {
            @Override
            protected Double initialize() {
                return Math.random();
            }
        };

        @Setup(Level.Trial)
        public void initialize() throws ConcurrentException {
            // Initialize
            guava.get();
            apache.get();
        }
    }

    @Benchmark
    public Double guavaCache(final CacheState state) {
        return state.guava.get();
    }

    @Benchmark
    public Double apacheCache(final CacheState state) throws ConcurrentException {
        return state.apache.get();
    }
}
```

